<p>This isn't really a horrifying/creepy SCP, I get that. But it seems to me that it would be a little more ominous if the reason there's dates on the labels is the same reason you date preserves &#8212; if you don't use them before a spoil date, they could go bad. Now, I'm not sure what &quot;spoiled weather&quot; looks like, but (in the US Northeast) Superstorm Sandy and (in the US South) Hurricane Katrina come to mind. What's more, if it spoils, maybe the weather patterns develop &quot;naturally&quot; &#8212; is that storm pattern over the Atlantic a normal Tropical Storm developing, or is Great-aunt June's &quot;Snow in July, 1905&quot; finally starting to turn?</p>
